HEADWORD: slipper orchid
<hw>slipper orchid</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any of several chiefly
American wildflowers having an inflated pouchlike lip; difficult or
impossible to cultivate in the garden.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lady's slipper, lady's-slipper,
lady-slipper.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slipperwort</ent>⟦br⟧
